A human Skull, aecompanied by the following Com- munication, was presented from Dr. Harlan, of Phila- delphia.—“ This skull is supposed to have belonged to an extinct race of Indians, which existed anterior to the present natives of the soil. This is inserred not only from some marked differences in the Skulls observed 011 compar-ison with those of our modern Indians, but also from the peculiarities of the utensils, both of war and cooking, found with the Skeletons, and which resemble more those of the South Americans or East Indians.
